wikipedia_page.main: James Jordan (born 21 June 1793 at Chatham, Kent; died 10 September 1866 at Chatham) was an English professional cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1822 to 1824.  He was mainly associated with Kent and made 9 known appearances in first-class matches, including 3 for the Players.
